cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on 3D pose estimation from single depth images using convolutional neural nets. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with articulated objects and their pose estimation, which is a common problem in robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel structured prediction approach using end-to-end training of neural nets. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with intelligent systems that can predict the optimal skeletal configuration of articulated objects. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with 3D pose estimation and skeletal models, which are relevant to computer graphics applications.
